    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>Map Control</h3>
      <p>Secure elevated positions, control narrow passages, and maintain sightlines that restrict enemy movement while enabling mutual support between teammates.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>Formation Discipline</h3>
      <p>Avoid clustering together to reduce vulnerability to explosives. Use staggered spacing and multi-angle coverage to prevent flanking.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>Tactical Flexibility</h3>
      <p>Sticking to one rigid tactic can lead to failure when opponents adapt. Adjust strategies like switching to flanking maneuvers as conditions warrant.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>Resource Conservation</h3>
      <p>Manage ammunition, healing items, and special abilities strategically rather than depleting them immediately.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card">
      <h3>Attack Timing</h3>
      <p>Coordinate pushes with proper timing — neither rushing recklessly nor delaying so long that enemies reinforce their positions.</p>
